Remarks — In the presence of pointed rostrum, lanceolate bothridial head with long setiform apex and developed notogastral setae, and in the absence of prolamella, the new species is similar to
Perscheloribates kontumensis Ermilov & Frolov, 2019
from Vietnam (see Ermilov & Frolov 2019a ), but differs from the latter by the presence of simple notogastral setae (versus with flexible tip in
P. kontumensis
) and the absence of body sculpturing (versus simple in
P. kontumensis
) and setae it on leg tarsi I–III (versus absent in
P. kontumensis
).
